This algorithm has a time complexity of O(log k) because in each recursive call, it eliminates approximately half of the elements from one of the lists. This makes it more efficient than the previous algorithm when k is much smaller than m and n. However, it can be less efficient when k is close to m + n, as it may need to make multiple recursive calls to eliminate all but the kth element.

